The Chronicle Mashudu Netsianda, Senior Reporter PRESIDENT Mnangagwa has arrived in Bulawayo ahead of tomorrow’s official opening of the 25th edition of the Mining, Engineering and Transport (Mine Entra) exhibition. <img class="alignnone wp-image-629698 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/07/ED4.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/07/ED4.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/07/ED4-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The President landed at the Joshua Mqabuko Nkomo International Airport aboard an Air Zimbabwe plane shortly before 7pm. <img class="alignnone wp-image-629695 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/07/ED1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/07/ED1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/07/ED1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> He was welcomed by Bulawayo Provincial Affairs and Devolution Minister Judith Ncube and Cabinet Ministers who included Minister of Mines & Mining Development Winston Chitando, Zanu Bulawayo provincial chairman Cde Jabulani Sibanda, Politburo member Cde Tshinga Dube and service chiefs among other high ranking Government officials Hundreds of Zanu-PF supporters were also part of the people who welcomed the President.  He also took time to greet the crowd before addressing them. 